The paper discusses the application of Compressed Sensing (CS) techniques to ultrasound imaging, which is a signal processing problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper deals with the processing of signals from biological tissues, which could place it in cs.BIO (Computational Biology and Bioinformatics) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
